# EXPLANATION OF FLAGS:
# --geometry 1920x1080: Forces the window to match your exact screen size.
# --scale-down: Large images shrink to fit the 1080p height/width.
# --auto-zoom: Small images stretch to fill the 1080p screen (See note below).
# --image-bg black: Adds black bars to fill empty space (instead of checkerboard).

default --geometry 1920x1080 --scale-down --image-bg black --draw-tinted
